The Truth Begins to Emerge=E2=80=9D that describes what, in securities =0Ac=
lass actions, is called the =E2=80=9Ccorrective disclosure.=E2=80=9D Chipot=
le did an earnings =0Acall saying that it expected its cost of sales to inc=
rease in the next quarter =0Aas =E2=80=9Can investment we are making as we =
focus on outlier restaurants to ensure =0Acorrect and generous portions,=E2=
=80=9D which is (arguably) an admission that in fact =0Ait was skimping on =
portions. And then the stock fell.=0A=0AThe lawsuit is =E2=80=9Ca class act=
ion on behalf of persons or entities who purchased =0Aor otherwise acquired=
 publicly traded Chipotle common stock between February 8, =0A2024 and Octo=
ber 29, 2024,=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cthe price of Chipotle stock fell $4.76 =
per =0Ashare, or 7.86%, to close at $55.73 on October 30, 2024,=E2=80=9D af=
ter profits fell =0Adue in part to increased costs for bigger portions. The=
re are 1.36 billion =0Ashares of Chipotle outstanding, times $4.76 is about=
 $6.5 billion in damages to =0Ashareholders. [5]  <>=0A=0AThat=E2=80=99s so=
